cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with spoken language understanding (SLU) system which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). It also involves tasks such as slot filling and intent detection which are common in NLP. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques to develop a joint model for the two tasks. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves the design of a new iteration mechanism to enhance the bi-directional interrelated connections between the tasks. 

cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely sub-category as the paper deals with spoken language understanding, but it could be relevant as it involves the processing of sound data. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a less likely sub-category as the paper involves the use of neural networks, but it is not the main focus of the paper.
